    "type": "message",
    "text": "1. The higher the ‘stakes’ the more important the need for statistics and deeper modern understanding. Industries like insurance DO use things like machine learning, but statistics helps them actually better stay compliant (e.g. you REALLY need to make sure you aren’t discriminating on things like race and sex). But hey if you’re just predicting which vacation rental someone is more likely to rent, lower stakes (and revenue, A/B testing, etc can be used as a ‘process’ to improve the system thru space and time)",
